	<h3>The Foundation: Human Ambition</h3>
	<p>
		My background is rooted in the humanities and public service. During my time in the Civil Service (Ministry of Defence) and my studies in Politics and Sociology, I learned how to navigate complex institutional structures and multi-level stakeholder relationships. From leadership in political campaigning to academic research in history and policy, I developed a deep understanding of the "why" behind how we organise our world.
	</p>

	<h3>The Architecture: Autonomous Systems</h3>
	<p>
		I am now translating that perspective into a technical toolkit. As a BSc AI & Data Science student at the University of Lancashire, I am building a foundation in Machine Learning, Systems Analysis, Database Design, and Frontier Tech.
	</p>

	<h3>The Bridge</h3>
	<p>
		I thrive in the space where research, ideation, and technical execution collide. I don’t just see code; I see the policy implications, the historical context, and the human impact. 
	</p>
